NBFC-UL's exposure to all its counterparties and groups of connected counterparties, excluding the exposures listed below, will be considered for exposure limits. The exposures that are exempted from the LEF are listed below:
a) Exposure to the Government of India and State Governments which are eligible for zero percent risk weight under capital regulations applicable to NBFC-UL;
b) Exposure where the principal and interest are fully guaranteed by the Government of India;
c) NBFC-UL's exposure to group entities that is deducted from its Owned Funds to arrive at the NOF.
d) Investment in the equity capital of the insurance company to the extent specifically permitted in writing by the Bank.

'Cash' to be maintained by a SFB shall include,
(i) cash in hand,
(ii)the net balance in current accounts with other scheduled commercial banks in India.
(iii) the deposit required under sub-section (2) of Section 11 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 to be made with the Reserve Bank by a banking company incorporated outside India;
(iv) any balance maintained by a scheduled bank with the Reserve Bank in excess of the balance required to be maintained by it under Section 42 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);
(v) any balances held by a bank with the RBI under the Standing Deposit Facility (SDF).

