(1) SEBI Registration;
(2) Membership of NSE/ BSE for debt market;
(3) Prior experience and Creditworthiness; and
(4) Market reputation, and details of regulatory action, if any.

An NBFC falling under the Middle Layer or Upper Layer shall have Board approved policies in place for the following:

(1) a policy for ascertaining the 'fit and proper' status of the directors at the time of appointment, and on a continuing basis, as detailed in paragraph 12 of these Directions;

(2) a policy laying down the role and responsibilities of the Chief Compliance Officer (CCO) with the objective of promoting a good compliance culture in the organization, as specified in paragraph 25(2) of these Directions;

(3) a compensation policy to address issues arising out of excessive risk taking caused by misaligned compensation packages, as detailed in paragraph 29 of these Directions; and

(4) reviews to be placed before the Board of the NBFC as given in paragraph 15 of these Directions.

